name: For Sale 2 Bedroom Unit near Skyway in Parañaque City! | DMCI Homes The Atherton
description:
DMCI Homes’ The Atherton development along Dr. A. Santos Avenue, Parañaque City, remains on track of its construction schedule and is slated to welcome its first batch of residents in August this year.

As of February this year, the construction of The Atherton’s first building, Oak, is already 91 percent complete and with such pace, is guaranteed to meet ready for occupancy (RFO) status by the second half of 2022. 

The 15-storey building is currently being dressed up in preparation for occupancy.

Construction of The Atherton’s two other 15-storey buildings, Helicia and Almond, is likewise making headway despite the limitations brought about by the coronavirus pandemic, thanks to DMCI Homes’ construction expertise and proficiency in project management.

Each building has an enhanced Lumiventt® Technology design as the balcony of every Sky Patio is extended. With the help of landscaped atriums and breezeways, more natural light and air permeate throughout the single-loaded corridors.

This healthy building design, coupled with one-, two-, and three-bedroom unit offerings ranging from 29 square meters (sq.m) to 91 sq.m, aims to provide residents spacious dwelling wellness for their evolving lifestyle needs.

Apart from the Oak building, some of the property’s amenities will also be ready for use when the first residents move in. These include the game area, multi-purpose area, entertainment room, as well as the Almond building’s ground floor lounge.

name: 1BR Condominium Unit for Sale at Azure Residences by Paris Hilton in Bicutan
description:
Featuring air-conditioned accommodation with a pool with a view, pool view and a balcony, Azure Urban Resort Residences - The Paris Hilton Beach Club is located in Manila. Situated on the beachfront, this property has a private beach area and a bar. The accommodation provides a 24-hour front desk and a lift for guests.  

The apartment with a terrace and sea views features 1 bedroom, a living room, a flat-screen TV, an equipped kitchen with a dishwasher and kitchenware, and 1 bathroom with an a bath or shower. For added privacy, the accommodation features a private entrance. 

Guests can go to the restaurant, while a grocery delivery service and a minimarket are also available.

Newport Mall is 10 km from the apartment, while Glorietta Mall is 12 km away. The nearest airport is Ninoy Aquino International, 8 km from Azure Urban Resort Residences - The Paris Hilton Beach Club, and the property offers a paid airport shuttle service.

name: For Sale: Woodsville Crest 1BR Condo Unit at Merville, Paranaque
description:
Live in a master-planned, low-density community, Woodsville Crest, where you can experience exclusive resort-style living within the Metro. With its nature-inspired amenities, spacious unit layouts of a studio, 1-bedroom, and 2-bedroom units, and smart home deliverables, you can recharge and rest at any moment's notice.


Located in a desirable location, Woodsville Crest is only a drive from Makati CBD, Alabang CBD, and Bonifacio Global City, ensuring convenient access to your work and recreational destinations. The community has ground-level amenities, with 60% dedicated to open spaces, and the two-story clubhouse is fully equipped with indoor and outdoor recreational areas. From game rooms to barbecue areas to co-working spaces, there is something for everyone to enjoy.

The building's interior has a beautifully designed layout featuring single-loaded corridors and an open atrium. Each unit comes with modern-day furnishings supportive of your desire for an upgraded home life in the suburbs and a dedicated space for your work-from-home set-up.

Woodsville Crest offers a well-rounded lifestyle with home innovations and features that make every day a vacation. With only nine floors per building, it offers exclusivity and privacy to future homeowners. The community incorporates sustainable development and unit features that make it environmentally sound, allowing residents to live harmoniously with nature.
Investing in Woodsville Crest is an excellent decision because of its accessible location, exclusivity, and privacy. Raise your standard of living and live in harmony with nature.

Contact your seller now for more details and avail of the launch promo for the unit of your choice. Price and availability are subject to change without prior notice—Reserve now for only a P40k reservation fee.

Marian Lakeview Park is located in San Martin de Porres, Paranaque. This exclusive subdivision is known for secured community and peaceful atmosphere that will make you excited to go home after. It is strategic location. Bounded by the cities of Taguig, Makati, Pasay, and Pateros, It brings you close to various metropolitan areas.

Why Buying a Property in the South of Metro Manila?

1. It Is a Rapidly Developing Urban Hub
It has its own central business district, shopping malls for both high end and mid-market, international schools, top-notch hospitals, and its own convenient access to the rest of southern Luzon.

2. It Is Near the Manila Airport
living in the south will cost less time to get to the airport than when traveling from the north. Since terminals of the Ninoy Aquino International Airports are just a short drive away from Muntinlupa, Parañaque, and Las Piñas

3. The Area Is Mostly Flood-free
Based on the findings of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources’ Mines and Geosciences Bureau, most of the flood-free to least flooded cities can be found in the south of Metro Manila. This can be attributed to the cities’ land slopes, effective drainage cleaning and maintenance, garbage and waste management, mandatory use of eco-friendly materials, implementation of carbon footprint deduction ways, and the area’s lush greeneries that help reduce risk of flooding.

4. Road infrastructure has made it very accessible to the rest of Metro Manila.
With roads such as the Southern Tagalog Arterial Road (STAR), Manila-Cavite Expressway, Muntinlupa-Cavite Expressway, South Luzon Expressway (SLEX), C5, and Skyway, getting to and from the South to the rest of Metro Manila and nearby provinces is fast and convenient.

5.The country’s premier schools are making its way to the South.
You won’t have to travel far to get quality education; there are a lot of excellent high schools and universities when you live in the South. Taguig is poised to become a university city as the University of the Philippines (UP) and De La Salle University (DLSU) are opening campuses in Bonifacio Global City (BGC). Make your way further down and you’ll find San Beda College and De La Salle Zobel in Alabang, Muntinlupa; Xavier School, DLSU, Don Bosco College, St. Scholastica’s College, Miriam School.

Marian Lakeview Park is located in San Martin de Porres, Paranaque. This exclusive subdivision is known for secured community and peaceful atmosphere that will make you excited to go home after. It is strategic location. Bounded by the cities of Taguig, Makati, Pasay, and Pateros, It brings you close to various metropolitan areas.

Why Buying a Property in the South of Metro Manila?

1. It Is a Rapidly Developing Urban Hub
It has its own central business district, shopping malls for both high end and mid-market, international schools, top-notch hospitals, and its own convenient access to the rest of southern Luzon.

2. It Is Near the Manila Airport
living in the south will cost less time to get to the airport than when traveling from the north. Since terminals of the Ninoy Aquino International Airports are just a short drive away from Muntinlupa, Parañaque, and Las Piñas

3. The Area Is Mostly Flood-free
Based on the findings of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources’ Mines and Geosciences Bureau, most of the flood-free to least flooded cities can be found in the south of Metro Manila. This can be attributed to the cities’ land slopes, effective drainage cleaning and maintenance, garbage and waste management, mandatory use of eco-friendly materials, implementation of carbon footprint deduction ways, and the area’s lush greeneries that help reduce risk of flooding.

4. Road infrastructure has made it very accessible to the rest of Metro Manila.
With roads such as the Southern Tagalog Arterial Road (STAR), Manila-Cavite Expressway, Muntinlupa-Cavite Expressway, South Luzon Expressway (SLEX), C5, and Skyway, getting to and from the South to the rest of Metro Manila and nearby provinces is fast and convenient.

5.The country’s premier schools are making its way to the South.
You won’t have to travel far to get quality education; there are a lot of excellent high schools and universities when you live in the South. Taguig is poised to become a university city as the University of the Philippines (UP) and De La Salle University (DLSU) are opening campuses in Bonifacio Global City (BGC). Make your way further down and you’ll find San Beda College and De La Salle Zobel in Alabang, Muntinlupa; Xavier School, DLSU, Don Bosco College, St. Scholastica’s College, Miriam School.

✔️Prestigious Education Facilities: BF Homes is home to prominent educational institutions such as Manresa School and De La Salle Zobel School.

name: Brand New 3-Storey House for Sale at Multinational Village, Parañaque City
description: Multinational Village Clean Chic Brand New 3-Storey Single Detached House and Lot for Sale in Moonwalk, Paranaque Nr. BF Homes, Sm Bicutan and Airport, Better Living  Code : DS883167 Category : For Sale Project : Multinational Village  City : Moonwalk, Paranaque  Unit : Five Bedroom 5BR Size : LA : 163 sqm FA : 378 sqm Parking : 2 Car Garage Selling Price : Php 25,000,000.00  Details  of the Property: •  Semi furnished •  Spacious Living and Dining Area •  Kitchen with Cabinets •  Service Area, Laundry and Drying Area •  All Bedrooms with Toilet and Bath •  Masters bedroom with walk-in closet •  Family Area / Entertainment Area •  Maid’s Room with Toilet and Bath •  Powder Room  •  Telephone and Cable Ready •  Complete Lighting and Bathroom Fixtures •  Terrace / Veranda  Multinational Village is a residential subdivision in Barangay Moonwalk, Parañaque. It’s considered one of the safest neighborhoods in Parañaque City, thanks to its attentive security services and low-density population. The village offers a wide variety of homes in a peaceful environment close to most essential establishments. Since it’s close to the central business districts of Makati, Pasay, Alabang, and Taguig, it’s a popular place for busy professionals to live.  Multinational Village Features and Amenities There are plenty of residential properties in Multinational Village for sale. Whether you’re in the market for a townhouse, a single-detached home, or a duplex, you’ll find it here. There are even homes with as many as fourteen bedrooms. Owning a property here is especially useful if you work in Makati, Las Piñas, Alabang, Pasay, and Cavite. These locations are highly accessible via C-5 Extension and the Metro Manila Skyway. You can also easily reach NAIAX and NAIA 1 to 4, roughly an hour and a half drive away.  Highlights of the Development You won’t have to travel far to stock up on essentials in Multinational Village in Moonwalk, Parañaque.  A stone’s throw away from the neighborhood is K Mart, SM City Sucat, Walter Mart Mall Sucat, and SM City Bicutan for all your shopping needs. It’s also an ideal place to raise children since there are plenty of top-notch schools in the vicinity, such as Sacred Heart School, Holy Francis School of Parañaque, and Madre Maria Pia Notari School.  Other Multinational Village Features Olivarez General Hospital, Parañaque Doctors’ Hospital, and Medical Center Parañaque are just a few minutes by car in case of emergency. At the same time, places of worship like Our Lady of the Most Holy Rosary Parish Church, San Agustin Parish Church, and Mary, Queen of Apostles Parish Church are also nearby if you enjoy going to church with your family on Sunday.  Nearby Landmarks SM Mall of Asia is only a few minutes away from the area. The extensive shopping and lifestyle center boasts retail stores, dining establishments, leisure centers, and sprawling events venues. The Metropolitan Museum, Cultural Center of the Philippines, and National Museum are also a short drive away. There are even more unique museums to check out nearby, such as The Desert Museum, Philippine Air Force Aerospace Museum, and Yexel’s Toy Museum. ARCA South is the next large-scale business and lifestyle district positioned to serve as the gateway to the south. It is strategically located in proximity to two of the country’s premier business districts, Makati and Bonifacio Global City.

WHY INVEST PROPERTY IN TAGUIG?

1. Best location.
When choosing an investment property, location is a huge factor. Taguig boasts of a very lively business and commercial environment, featuring:
-16 commercial banks and 10 rural banks
-1,126 manufacturing firms
-243 restaurants
-2 shopping malls
-24 cottage industries
-7,776 registered commercial establishments
-53 subdivisions

2. Easily accessible.
Taguig has become a major landmark in Metro Manila and there are several ways to get to this master-planned city. People can travel via EDSA, C5, Kalayaan Avenue, or Makati City. A faster route would be going through the McKinley Road from the West or the Villamor Airbase from the South.

3. 24-hour security
In a crazy city like Metro Manila, security is often a serious problem, even in gated communities or cities. Hence, Taguig invested heavily in round-the-clock security for its dwellers.

4. Low tax rates.
Taguig has one of the lowest tax rates in Metro Manila. The Taguig Revenue Code contains provisions that implement lower local taxes on banks, insurance companies, hotels, telecom, pharmaceuticals, software companies, car dealers, and manufacturing firms. This move was designed to encourage more investors to come to Bonifacio Global City and generate more income. Banks in Taguig, for example, are charged with an 8% tax compared to Quezon City’s 25% and Makati City’s 15%.

name: For Sale 1-Bedroom Unit at Azure Urban Resort Residences Miami Tower, Parañaque
description:
Azure Urban Resort Residences was designed by the award-winning masterplanning and architectural firm Broadway Malyan with each tower set in a breathtaking tropical modern setting that provides optimal natural ventilation, light, and shade.

A kidney bean-shaped clubhouse complements an organically formed lustrous landscape that capitalizes on the uniqueness of an artificial beach. This in turn asserts a sense of identity and legibility to the different character areas within the 6-hectare site.

Other amenities like an open park, zen garden, multiple playgrounds, lap pool with cascading waterfalls, kiddie water slide, poolside bar, beach volleyball area and a basketball court have been incorporated into the master plan, adding rich diversity to a natural environment that supports recreation, health and well being.

Price: PHP4,000,000

WITH TENANT UNTIL November 2024

AMENITIES:
THE AZURE BEACH
The true centerpiece of the Azure Urban Resort Residences is the Azure Beach – an iconic man-made beach facility with fine white sand, undulating waves and waterfalls.
THE BEACH BAR
The Azure Beach Bar is a dynamic hangout in the middle of the Azure beach. Breezy and well-stocked with light snacks and an assortment of beverages, it also houses a DJ deck for day jams and night parties.
THE AZURE CHILDREN’S BEACH PLAYGROUND
The beach playground features an engaging water play area with fun kiddie slides and large buckets that fill and empty themselves every few minutes, as well as valves designed for releasing spurts of water.

description: United Paranaque Subdivision | Prime Residential Lot for Sale in San Isidro, Paranaque City near Ninoy Aquino Airport, BF Homes, BGC and Makati CBD Code : DS882839 Category : For Sale Project : United Paranaque Subdivision City : San Isidro, Paranaque City Size : 317 sqm Price per sqm : Php 50,473.18 Selling Price : Php 16,000,000.00 NET Details of the Property: • Clean Title • Facing South west • Near Arca South • Near in highly commercialize area United Paranaque Subdivision is located in San Isidro, Paranaque. This exclusive subdivision is known for secured community and peaceful atmosphere that will make you excited to go home after. It is strategic location. Bounded by the cities of Taguig, Makati, Pasay, and Pateros, It brings you close to various metropolitan areas.  Why Buying a Property in the South of Metro Manila?  1. It Is a Rapidly Developing Urban Hub It has its own central business district, shopping malls for both high end and mid-market, international schools, top-notch hospitals, and its own convenient access to the rest of southern Luzon.  2. It Is Near the Manila Airport living in the south will cost less time to get to the airport than when traveling from the north. Since terminals of the Ninoy Aquino International Airports are just a short drive away from Muntinlupa, Parañaque, and Las Piñas  3. The Area Is Mostly Flood-free Based on the findings of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources’ Mines and Geosciences Bureau, most of the flood-free to least flooded cities can be found in the south of Metro Manila. This can be attributed to the cities’ land slopes, effective drainage cleaning and maintenance, garbage and waste management, mandatory use of eco-friendly materials, implementation of carbon footprint deduction ways, and the area’s lush greeneries that help reduce risk of flooding.  4. Road infrastructure has made it very accessible to the rest of Metro Manila. With roads such as the Southern Tagalog Arterial Road (STAR), Manila-Cavite Expressway, Muntinlupa-Cavite Expressway, South Luzon Expressway (SLEX), C5, and Skyway, getting to and from the South to the rest of Metro Manila and nearby provinces is fast and convenient.  5.The country’s premier schools are making its way to the South. You won’t have to travel far to get quality education; there are a lot of excellent high schools and universities when you live in the South. Taguig is poised to become a university city as the University of the Philippines (UP) and De La Salle University (DLSU) are opening campuses in Bonifacio Global City (BGC). Make your way further down and you’ll find San Beda College and De La Salle Zobel in Alabang, Muntinlupa; Xavier School, DLSU, Don Bosco College, St. Scholastica’s College, Miriam School, and UP in Laguna; and DLSU campuses in Dasmarinas, Cavite and in Lipa, Batangas. ✔️Benefits of Living in a Bungalow House 

✅Accessibility: Bungalows are typically single-story homes, providing easy access for individuals of all ages and abilities, including seniors and those with mobility issues. 
✅No Stairs: With no stairs to navigate, bungalows are ideal for families with young children and for individuals who prefer or require a stair-free living environment. 
✅Energy Efficiency: Single-story homes often have a more efficient heating and cooling system, as there is no need to circulate air between multiple levels. 
✅Easier Maintenance: With all living spaces on one level, maintenance tasks such as cleaning and repairs can be more straightforward compared to multi-story homes. 
✅Natural Light: Single-story homes often have larger windows and more direct access to natural light, enhancing the overall brightness and openness of the living spaces. 
✅Future-Proofing: Bungalows can be adapted for future needs, such as adding accessibility features or converting spaces without dealing with multiple levels. 
✅Outdoor Living: Bungalow designs often include easy access to outdoor spaces like gardens or patios, providing opportunities for outdoor relaxation and entertainment. 
✅Adaptability: Bungalows can be suitable for various lot sizes and shapes, offering flexibility in choosing a property.

Marian Lakeview Park is located in Arca South, Western Bicutan, Taguig. This exclusive subdivision is known for secured community and peaceful atmosphere that will make you excited to go home after. It is strategic location. Bounded by the cities of Taguig, Makati, Pasay, and Pateros, It brings you close to various metropolitan areas.

Why Buying a Property in the South of Metro Manila?

1. It Is a Rapidly Developing Urban Hub
It has its own central business district, shopping malls for both high end and mid-market, international schools, top-notch hospitals, and its own convenient access to the rest of southern Luzon.

2. It Is Near the Manila Airport
living in the south will cost less time to get to the airport than when traveling from the north. Since terminals of the Ninoy Aquino International Airports are just a short drive away from Muntinlupa, Parañaque, and Las Piñas

3. The Area Is Mostly Flood-free
Based on the findings of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources’ Mines and Geosciences Bureau, most of the flood-free to least flooded cities can be found in the south of Metro Manila. This can be attributed to the cities’ land slopes, effective drainage cleaning and maintenance, garbage and waste management, mandatory use of eco-friendly materials, implementation of carbon footprint deduction ways, and the area’s lush greeneries that help reduce risk of flooding.

4. Road infrastructure has made it very accessible to the rest of Metro Manila.
With roads such as the Southern Tagalog Arterial Road (STAR), Manila-Cavite Expressway, Muntinlupa-Cavite Expressway, South Luzon Expressway (SLEX), C5, and Skyway, getting to and from the South to the rest of Metro Manila and nearby provinces is fast and convenient.

5.The country’s premier schools are making its way to the South.
You won’t have to travel far to get quality education; there are a lot of excellent high schools and universities when you live in the South. Taguig is poised to become a university city as the University of the Philippines (UP) and De La Salle University (DLSU) are opening campuses in Bonifacio Global City (BGC). Make your way further down and you’ll find San Beda College and De La Salle Zobel in Alabang, Muntinlupa; Xavier School, DLSU, Don Bosco College, St. Scholastica’s College, Miriam School.
